text: WARNING,THIS IS MY OPINION, IF YOU DONT AGREE YOU CAN DO SO IN A CALM MANOR AND NOT BE AN INTERNET THUG, THNAK YOU:  Sigh....Akira Toriyama is really bad at making new forms lol. I shouldve learned my lesson and not gotten excited for his new form, especially with the extreme disapointment of "Super Saiyan God" a.k.a Kaioken Times 1,000,000. Like a recolor...realy? Ok whatever. So he becomes like super saiyan color, Frieza becomes the monkey that he so very much hates....whatever. Im just disappointed. I didnt like battle of gods at all, and i had high hopes for htis movie, now im goin in with low expectations so hopefully ill like it cause my extremely low and negative outlook on this movie will be surpassed. He did say a looong time ago and recently that Super Saiyan was upposed to be the pinnacle of strength and he regrets creating ss2 and 3 and all that, but for ppl that grew up with DBZ that was amazing. And because of that statement, its probably the reason ssg was a recolor, and now friezas new form is just a recolor. I was hoping maybe he'd look something like coolers final form but better, but obviously Toriyama is walking down a road of whta hes always wanted dbz to be, and id be fine with that if the new stuff wasnt stupid. Whatever though, i hope this movie will be good, cause if not im just gonna continue to say dbz from raditz to Buu is amazing and pretend battle of ass and return of friezas ass dont exist.

text: I cant understand anything thats said- but here be my theory (spoiler from part 1 special manga) but because of Frieza's old fear of super saiyans, having faced one, and now having a more mature understanding of the situation he would be in if he fought goku and friends after knowing they(he) defeated majin buu,  It makes me think that he underwent some process of adding sayian blood to his body- or the gene that allows a super sayain transformation, but took it to a different branch level.  His golden recolor is all im going off off, but if you've read the 1st part chapter, he's deff. aware he isnt 'the shit', like he did during namek. and understands he needs to train- but  realizing that super saiyans may be one of the strongest things in the universe(for defeating buu and being afraid of buu), his only option to defeating them, would be to become 'like' one.  He's thrown away his pride of natural perfection and has accepted change as a means to victory? maybe even some under lined respect now too- like a DIO to Johnathan joestar scenario.  genetic mods have been a constant theme thru Dragon Ball too, so... maybe? thats my theory.

text: -The Gohan screenshot can be explained easily, he see's Frieza and attacks him, thinking he is still the same power he was when he last fought him, however Frieza utterly destroy's Gohan and actually kills him(come on Gohan is clearly dead he has no pupils, like other people when they die in DBZ he was never revived with the Earth Dragon Balls so this can happen). This would give Goku motivation to kill Frieza as well.  -We clearly see Future Trunks killing Frieza and in the manga that has been released Frieza says he want's revenge on both of the saiyans who beat him(Goku and Trunks). With Frieza's new form Goku is evenly matched with him while Vegeta is utterly outclassed and afraid of Frieza's new power. While this is happening Goten and Trunks(present) arrive to assist in fighting Frieza's army since you know there is a thousand of them. After seeing Trunks Frieza believes it is the same one and moves into kill him. At this point Frieza offers to spar Trunks if Vegeta rejoins him as his servant. Vegeta does so and joins Frieza in the fight against Goku. Now The New God Frieza and Vegeta beat Goku(would explain Vegeta looking down angrily looking down at the beaten Goku with his back to a laughing Frieza.) and prepare to destroy the Earth however Beerus and Whis jump in and finish off what is left of Frieza's army and Beerus fights both Frieza and Vegeta while Whis restores Goku to full power and asks him to assist Beerus so he doesn't get carried away. Goku now enraged of Vegeta's betrayal and having just learned of Gohan's death powers back up to SSJG and smashes Vegeta and takes over for Beerus and with Beerus they together kill God Frieza. Vegeta is left in a broken state and everyone is ashamed of him for siding with Frieza with his friendship with all of them being strained as well. As a token of appriciation to Goku and his friends Beerus and Whis due to being God's request to the otherworld to restore Gohan's life back for his effort in defending Earth.

text: At first I thought Frieza's new form was lame, but then after watching it in action, it's actually pretty cool. The gold to signify the pinnacle of his races' transformations to mirror the gold that signified his nemesis, the Saiyans, pinnacle form is a perfect fit in my eyes. Also I don't see why people were expecting some crazy looking big bad form for Frieza. Toriyama's style was always final form = subtle less aggressive looking than the rest. Look at Cell, Buu, God Goku, or even Beerus the God of Destruction is just a skinny cat. You could say yeah look at Cooler and Broly but they were just fun side projects.  So yeah I dig it. His new form had to be less aggressive looking than his final form 100% but also had to say, "You're about to get your ass kicked." And we all know thanks to SSj1 2 and 3 that more gold means more ass kicking and from what I saw..... Frieza is sporting a whooooooooole lot of gold.

text: You know, i stopped being fan DBZ long time ago, but the last movie, z and the newly released xenoverse, and multiverse fan-comic, got me back at liking the dbz again, even if only a little.   This movie, while first thought i wondered like all of you, "huh, Frieza? but isnt he weak nowdays?" but here is the thing. If goku and others can get stronger with seemingly no effort (looking at all the transformations, fusions, namek fusing, and all that power level BS), then why cant Frieza do the same? and heck, its actually belieable, that he trains to achieve new powers, just like our heroes done billions of time before, so it inst impossible.  At first, i also thought his new form is lame as heck, and desing wise, it is, then thinking again... now he actually looks like cooler.... so cooler's previous form was like Frieza's then current final form.... so Frieza can still have form(s) even further?  plus, frieza as character and villain is simple and entertaining and i defninedly am gonna check this movie out.  PS: I also now remembered why i left the fandom in the first place. Not because of dbz itself, but it was because  of pretty much rest fandom's obnoxity and toxicity (excluding maybe one or few people). text: I keep seeing people complaining about Friezas new form. First of all, its not just a simple "color change". Anyone who's kept up with the series should know that its not about the looks of someone, its about the power they hold! None of the villains in the series looked all that impressive in terms of size and image, but boy were they powerful! Frieza, Cell, Buu,ect, the Z warriors would always comment on how weak they looked, but they always got their asses handed to them! Hell, even Beerus himself looks unintimidating! The same goes for this movie. Sure Friezas ne form doesnt look much different and monsterous, but his POWER increased beyond imagining! You saw for yourself in the trailer, Goku got his ass whipped, and it takes MASSIVE amounts of power for that to happen! Even god-like power like in the last movie! Thats what its all about, you dont have to look strong to BE strong! So please, stop bitching about the form, and get hyped for the AWESOME battle ahead! My hype level is over 9000! If all you're doing is complaining, your hype level is is only...5.

text: @TragedyStrikes(can't comment on my own post for some reason) No superiority approach. Just trying to show the flaw in your stinky logic. If you didn't read my book, then go read it. It has a lot of valuable information on it.   Yeah, you tried way too hard on this, and the end result wasn't beneficial for you. I don't know how you got the "and now" mixed up. You obviously did it to twist my words, but that's fine, I still forgive you. "And now" means that Freeza has been changed to look like an exact copy of his brother's original form (the one we first see), only a different colour. Why did I write this, you may ask? Simple, you foolish duck! Because he looks exactly like Cooler, only painted a different colour (and here's the kicker) DESPITE STATING TO HAVE A TRANSFORMATION. Cooler's 4th form (which would be the equivalent to Freeza's 4th form) looks similar to Freeza's "final form", but there are certain differences that a monkey could tell the difference. Cooler's 5th form changed him completely. Freeza's "transformation" didn't change him, it only painted him a different colour. Basically, what I'm saying is that there's a difference between looking similar, and looking like a 99% copy, only a different colour. This has nothing to with them being siblings (obviously, I know they would have to look the same, because they're siblings). Here, I'll make it more simple for you, whore:   Freeza's final form (4th form)/ Cooler's 4th form (initial form we see on the big screen [that is, if you even have a big screen. I got a 72' plasma ACDC TV, with NOS, and a camshaft exhaust that would put your brick TV to shame, son.]}= roughly the same (due to being siblings), but having minor differences.   Cooler's 5th form (final form)/Freeza's "new transformation"= Cooler having an actual new form, whereas Freeza changed to look exactly like his older brother, only painted differently.   Did you get that? Take some, call your parents, hire a tutor, etc...If you still can't grasp my "superior" knowledge, and then come back for some more training, asshopper.   *"You're complaining that SSG looks too much like Kaoken despite transformations before looking similar (which you oh so gracefully ignored)."*  I stated to many people that's that what I see. SSJ wasn't as creative, but for the time it came out, it was a big change. This is a 20+ year-old character, who finally gets a new transformation, only to have him painted gold. Wow, look at the creativity in that. Deviant Art's been doing a much better job. So, no, I didn't ignore them, you just didn't read my books I published in the comments above. If you'd like, I can wire you some Zenny to hire that tutor. I want you to grow big and strong, and become smart, like the 235+ people who agreed with me that this "transformation" is shit.   The rest was insults, so here's one for you:   Riddle me here, riddle me there, who just got destroyed, and looked foolish? text: People bitching about the ''transformations''. They're not even transformations guys.. It's like an unlocked potential thing. It's not a transformation, just like mystic gohan is NOT a transformation. Goku doesn't even have the ''God transformation'' anymore. He absorbed most, if not all, into his base power. That's why you do not see the red ki anymore. That was just a moment to display he became a Saiyan god at that moment. As you can see in this trailer, he has regular white ki.   To be honest, I really enjoy what they're doing. All those silly forms and stuff and people expecting extreme over the top transformations is just insane. Why would you even want that? I love the subtle forms. Freeza's colouring could've been done differently, but he should not have had a new transformation. Why? Because his race uses transformations to supress power, not gain it. Freeza's ''final form'' is actually his actual regular form. This ''form'' is just a recolouring of that final form that he's supposed to look like.  You people know nothing about dbz.  Also don't bring in Cooler, he's non canon, created by people who clearly had no idea or had no regard for the idea how Freeza's race works.

text: You know what? I don't blame Toriyama on making his new form like this. You know why? Fakes. Fakes all over the place. People make these flashy designs for frieza in hopes of something even better. You need to understand that if someone even comes close to the design Toriyama has in mind,he has to start all over again,and only God knows how many times THAT happened.  Besides,just think about it. Being a God doesn't mean worrying about your looks. It means that you have a responsibility to use all the power that you have in your own way.   Give Toriyama a break guys. He's aged over the years,so he's lost a good bit of his creativity and imagination. Be grateful that DBZ is still even around.  -BritoBurrito

text: Was battle of gods and revival of f the only cannon movies besides the dead zone? If so thats just dumb. All the other movies, with the exception of one or two, could be easily peiced together with the normal timeline. Yes there are a lot of details in the movies that are out of place and contridict the normal story but if yuo realy think about it all those out of place details are small changes to characters and differences in the background. They add that stuff so it can be a full length movie. they would get more money from that rather than just including them into the series. And you cant just say its "not cannon" because toriama didnt write certain movies. the same thing goes for DBGT. that show might have a few plot holes and what not but its practically the end to DBZ. Plus it came out before these new movies. One of the biggest reasons people are saying DBGT is not cannon is only because these new movies slightly contradict the events of that show. But enogh ranting. I also think that everyone is just supposed to look at the whole story in which the way they please. All of this is just my opinion. not fact.

text: I think this movie will make me feel some mixed feelings. We will get to see the Z warriors actually kicking some butt for once. I didn’t notice this before, but we will also see Piccolo and Gohan get owned by one of Freiza Henchmen. My money is that it is a transformed Sorbet.  I originally felt that Gohan would defeat Sorbet and get Knocked out by Freiza, but that battle may go a bit different now. Gohan went Super Saiyan in this movie, most likely because his power kept decreasing to the point he needs to use it again to remain relevant. I don’t think Vegeta will finish off Freiza, which will disappoint many fans. He will help, but I am not sure he will get the satisfying killing blow. We have not seen Goku fight Freiza in Super Saiyan form for some reason. You would think he would have transformed into a Super Saiyan after witnessing his power, but ok. We don’t know what Vegeta and Freiza battle is going to look like.  I had many other opinions, but actually watching and paying attention to the new movie trailer, I am not so sure anymore. Another concern of mine will Vegeta actually gets to go Super Saiyan God. The requirements are five Saiyan transfer their powers into one body, but everyone kind of look busy. Another oddity is Trunks and Goten left out of the movie, are they going to be left out of a movie due to some weird plot device, like they were having nap time when the fight took place or something?

text: There is seriously no pleasing you damn fans. I'm perfectly fine with the new Frieza look as long as the storyline fits and makes sense, I don't need to him to go all Cooler like with his new transformation. Simplicity is the way to go after years of crazy transformations in the series. Be grateful that the guy is at least willing to revive the series through movies, don't complain and whine. My ONLY problem is the fact that funimation takes so damn long to acquire the rights to dub the film. Its released everywhere else on the same date, and I would love for funimation to follow that process so that fans in the US don't have to wait almost two years for a dub.  This is why a new series is a horrible idea, because the fans will always just bitch about how this is too simple, this is too complex, this is too this, too that. SSG was fine too, but you guys probably wanted some crazy purple blue orange mix colored ssj3 style hair. This looks promising, especially with the role that Vegeta is gonna play. Bring on the next movie in 2017, keep em coming as long as they make sense. But hey, knowing you fans, you probably won't be happy with Vegeta's new look either (rumored blue hair blue aura) or whatever it is.
author: Jose Gomez

text: I respect other fans' (or perhaps just trolls) opinion but for me Frieza is the most deserving villain to be revived. He is the most classic villain in the series. Making him significant again is a good move to revive Dragon Balls' popularity at its peak. Besides, many fans still could not accept how human made androids were stronger than a galactic tyrant. Now, Frieza got the position he deserved.

text: The thing about DBZ is that Toriyama always tried to surprise people by avoiding the obvious. That worked great when people expected lameness, but now that that's not the case, this mentality is sadly working in the opposite direction. You see, when people expected something predictable and lame, he would come up with something surprising and epic, but now people expect nothing less than epicness from DBZ, and he knows that, just like he knew everyone expected Goku to win the first tournaments. What does he do then? The same he always did: the opposite. See the problem now? He's intentionally avoiding the epic and impressive because that's what people expect.  As a consequence of all of that, we got that lame SSJG transformation, Beerus' pudding fight, Vegeta's ridiculous dance, Vegeta's brother, Vegeta's brother's wife, and now this childish new form for Frieza and the idiotic explanation they came up with to justify Frieza's unexplainable power("oh he's a prodigy, so he's super strong!"). Not to mention the new gaping plot hole regarding the fact that Shenron cannot revive people after more than one year after their death.  Why is that a problem? Because it's turning DBZ into a joke.
author: dante meriere

text: The over-the-top designs ruined any future for the show. If DBZ kept going, it would have had to keep "one upping" the last ssj transformation till we got some seriously ridiculous shit. But what we got was subtle, and leaves room for moderate growth in future transformations if somehow DBZ keeps going. I'm so sick of hearing people complain Frieza and ssjg isnt "badass" enough. Nowadays anime has to be badass with badass characters and anything slow or subtle is considered shit.

text: Man, this'll be awesome. I have some questions but I'm sure they'll be answered once I can watch the movie.  1.) After all the hype of SSJGod and "god power" in general, it's rather amazing and weird for me to see Frieza attain that level of power. I'm gonna rationalize it this way; There are certain species that have the potential to attain god power. The ones we've seen are Beeris' race, Whis' race, Saiyans and apparently Frieza's race. If the existence of a god of destruction is the way of the universe, then logically organisms that can BE that god must exist. Just like Goku attained god power through accessing SSJGod mode, Frieza's race manifests god power in that gold transformation like SSJGod was red. It would explain why Beerus would be so concerned with Frieza.  2.) Despite this, how could Goku be defeated so handily? From what we see in this video, Goku pushes Frieza to go into his god mode and it appears that Goku hung with it for some time before Frieza finally overwhelmed him. However, when Goku fought Beerus as a SSJGod the form eventually ran out. His body surpassed the limit and was able to contend with Beerus after. He went SSJ during the fight to continue. In interviews Toriyama said he'll do away with the extra SSJ forms like SSJ2-3, making the characters concentrate more on mastering base SSJ state. Considering this, Goku would've likely trained to that principle and he can still transform just as he did with Beerus. That means the base Goku should still be of godly power and going SSJ would only multiply his power YET we see that he never went SSJ, he stuck to base form. Hopefully this is explained because SSJ is still a thing in Battle of Gods and he should be able to defeat Frieza's gold form with it no problem, considering he fought with the gold form in his own base form before being defeated.  We shall see!

text: You see, you know what makes fans such as myself love the new look of Golden Frieza? there are three major factors here, the Iconic characters, The Story, and the music, this is what drives you to except as a "Fan" to appreciate what Akira toriyama and the people behind this are doing. Akira toriyama chose Frieza's new look as Optimum, this is not an "Opinion" this is common sense based on Akira Toriyama's perception, he didn't want to change frieza's over all shape, but to introduce small touches to him, Frieza really didn't change much, only the color of his skin and the outer part of it, he looks astounding and royal looking.  As for the story? and I'm sure many will agree, Vegeta has to be the one and only to take Frieza down once and for all! I will never forget his last words when Frieza took his life on Namek...   From Dragon Ball Z Kai.  Vegeta: "Please Kakarot you have to listen to me! I need you to know what happened to planet Vegeta, where we were born! It's gone, destroyed! that's true, but not... not cause it collided with a giant meteor... it was Frieza! Frieza did it! after we saiyans served him faithfully, and blindly followed his every last order he' he betrayed us he disposed of our race like common trash wiped us from existence... so that now, we are all that remain, there all gone! your parents, my father the king... we saiyan's were growing In strength and numbers and Frieza feared that soon a super saiyan will be born among us.. It terrified him! I'm begging you please... beat him! for me! for the pride of our race... you must defeat him.... please.... he must die by a saiyan's hand..."

text: Terrible artwork. Not sure why DBZ's key animation has been given off to such slouches these last ten years or so. DBZ move art was always great, if you track the movies from 11, 12, 13 and compare them to this and Battle of Gods it's clear how much of a downgrade has occured. I don't understand why nobody seems to notice how bad it's gotten. I feel like I'm in an episode of the twilight zone or x files. I love DBZ, I've been a fan for over 20 years; I'm excited that it's being revived but I can't stand how poor a job is being done artistically. Story is fine, overall concept and storyboard too, but the artwork and animation isn't. Everything is off scale, during an animation sequence proportions of arms and faces are constantly in flux, there's no texture or depth in any of the background art... colors are all flat. Momoclo's all this production's got going for it.

text: People don't like the idea of Vegeta being able to do what Goku cannot, simply due to the element of Goku being a unique Saiyan with powers achievable through morally pure means, where Vegeta was a self-concerned Saiyan Prince, humbled by a "low class" subordinate. He (Vegeta) was proven to not be as powerful as his title suggests because the old-world Saiyan hierarchy is no longer relevant; the new-world Saiyan line-up are based on Earth, and protecting it is now what defines their people.  Vegeta has the chance now to surpass Goku if need-be, because he has a stake in the planet Earth, as well as facing the man who killed his people. The accumulation of destroying Planet Vegeta (which was not relevant to Goku as he never knew it as his home), as well as the threat on Earth all amounts to Fireza's presence before Vegeta. Frieza seeks to eradicate Vegeta's new planet, but now that he truly has something to defend (his family, his allies, and his home), the stakes are raised, and Vegeta has the opportunity not only to avenge his people once and for all, but save Earth from the same fate.  That's called a story arc, and would probably best-suit the film's narrative. But if you guys wanna just see Goku overcome a bad buy again.... *shrug*

text: FINALLY GUYS Detailed Summary of Revivial of F. Down in Hell, a gaggle of cute angels and stuffed animals crowd around a lone tree in a verdant field. Encased in a pod suspended from the tree’s branches is Freeza, looking thoroughly displeased. Sorbet, the de facto leader of Freeza’s remaining forces, reluctantly orders their withdrawal from Planet 448 as the inhabitants rebel. He inquires of his soldiers’ progress in locating the Namekians’ new planet, but in spite of their many spy robots, they have found nothing. In disgust, he orders Tagoma, his top lieutenant, to accompany him to Earth to return Lord Freeza to life! From orbit, Sorbet and Tagoma see that someone besides “that woman” can collect Dragon Balls, and this group already has six! Bringing the Pilaf Trio aboard, the group goes on to obtain the seventh ball at the bottom of the ocean. Elsewhere, Piccolo is babysitting an infant Pan in front of Mr. Satan’s mansion, rocking her cradle with his foot. Videl and Gohan apologize for being late as Piccolo acts embarrassed. He suddenly notices an unusual ki in the distance. In a rocky, barren landscape, Sorbet orders Pilaf to summon Shenlong, and orders that Lord Freeza be returned to life! Though Shenlong initially resists reviving a chopped-up body, the minions go through with it anyway. Freeza’s body lands in a pile of chunks in front of them. The Dragon then demands a second wish, so Shuu hastily wishes for one million zenny. The Dragon takes its leave, leaving Sorbet and Tagoma to collect the pieces of Freeza before departing. Freeza pieces himself back together in a healing chamber on Sorbet’s ship. Freeza emerges in his first form, surveying his surroundings. Sorbet hastily introduces himself, as do his lieutenants Tagoma and Shisami, who Sorbet claims are equal in ability to the late Zarbon and Dodoria. Sorbet suggests reviving his father as well, but Freeza refuses, citing “Papa’s” egotism. After killing a random minion and grousing about the state of his own power, Freeza says it will take some time before his revenge. Tagoma attempts to reason with him, suggesting that it would be wiser to simply ignore the Saiyans; Freeza lifts him up telekinetically, then tosses him through the viewport into space. Soldiers are sucked out into the vacuum, as Sorbet orders the shields raised. Sorbet attempts to explain that Son Goku has become much, much stronger since their last encounter, but in spite of this massive power-up, Freeza, who has never trained before in his life, believes that if he trains for a few months, he will be able to surpass even that Saiyan…! After a brief argument with a Capsule Corporation receptionist, Jaco, a member of the Galactic Patrol, is able to meet up with his old friends Dr. Brief and Bulma. Jaco says he’s heard that she was friends with the one who defeated Freeza… who has been revived, and is on his way to Earth with a thousand soldiers! Bulma attempts to summon Whis through a strawberry sundae offering, but when nothing happens, she decides to let everyone know about the situation herself. Kuririn’s arrest of two thugs is interrupted by a call from Bulma. He hurries home to prepare, where he puts on his dōgi, and gets No. 18 to shave his head. He tells his wife and daughter to stay safe. As he flies away, No. 18 whispers, “So cool….” Goku and Vegeta are sparring against Whis. While both appear to be going all-out, neither is able to touch him, and when they attempt to attack in tandem, they merely get in each other’s way. Both are thinking before they attack; they need to let their bodies take the initiative and act. Vegeta is always tense and slow to react, while Goku is too relaxed and open to attack. At this point, Beerus appears: he can’t get any sleep with that racket going on. He sneezes, and sends an energy ball hurtling towards a nearby planet, which explodes. Whis complains about the time that he had to fix Beerus’ destruction of several nearby suns. Goku is surprised, and asks if Whis can create worlds, but Whis says he can merely rewind time a bit and do things over. Vegeta asks what he is; Whis supposes he is… a life-form called “Whis”. Back on Earth, Freeza’s ship arrives, and troops spill out. Earth’s fighters can feel Freeza’s ki and head in that direction, but not before he, as a greeting, obliterates North City with a single blast. Gohan purposely avoided telling Goten and Trunks about the impending fight because the two of them might do something rash. Freeza notices the heroes, and singles out the one he remembers killing on Namek. A spaceship arrives and Bulma hops out. She wastes no time in unloading a verbal barrage on Freeza, who responds asking where Son Goku is. She engages in provocation until Kuririn points out to her that Freeza has in fact gotten much, much stronger, like he’s a different person. She quickly changes her tune and asks for Freeza to wait until Son-kun shows up, but when Freeza gives only 10 seconds, she unloads on him again. Freeza unleashes his army, while each hero is forced to engage multiple enemies at a time. Freeza dryly notes that Earth’s fighters are intentionally avoiding killing their foes. As the crowd of soldiers thins, Piccolo is taken on directly by Shisami, who proves a more formidable challenge than the others. Gohan steps in, however, and makes quick work of him after becoming a Super Saiyan. Sorbet is horrified, and Freeza says he didn’t know how truly fearsome a Super Saiyan was. Earth’s fighters take a senzu each to recover from their fight. Freeza laments the pitiable state of his forces, as one soldier apologizes for being no match for the Earthlings. Freeza comments that their lying around like that is an eyesore, and dispatches them all in an instant. Freeza eyes Gohan and knocks him down with a single blast. Kuririn panics when he realize that Gohan has no pulse. There’s no way for him to eat a senzu like this, either…! Piccolo uses a kiai as a form of chest-compression which gets Gohan’s heart beating and enables him to down the second-to-last senzu. The Oracle Fish shows up to tell Whis that there was a message for him earlier. Whis is excited at the thought of there being something tasty waiting for him, but his joy is quickly interrupted by Bulma shouting at him for not getting back earlier and that Freeza has returned. Whis notes that it would take 35 minutes, but Bulma interrupts to tell Goku to just teleport there already! Goku tells Vegeta to hurry up and grab his hand, which flusters him. Goku reminds him that if they don’t hurry, Bulma might get killed, and he reluctantly puts his hand in Goku’s. The two of them disappear from Beerus’ planet. Goku teleports to Earth, and Vegeta hastily lets go of his hand. Freeza speaks of his suffering in Hell, but at last the day of his revenge has arrived. He can’t bear the thought of Son Goku alive, to the point that he trained for the first time in his life. Goku says his power has indeed increased, but he himself has also gotten a lot stronger. Freeza acknowledges that he was caught a bit off-guard, but no matter: this time, he will start fighting right in his final form! Goku is impressed, and comments that if Freeza weren’t such an evil guy, he’d make a good rival. This just annoys Freeza even further. After a moment, he also expresses his confusion at Goku’s lack of a Super Saiyan transformation. Goku responds that he does not need to. The two clash, and while the fighting is fierce, it becomes clear to the others that Freeza hasn’t landed a single hit. Freeza who attacks with a renewed ferocity. However, Goku is not seriously perturbed, and Vegeta starts to get annoyed. Eventually, he flies up to where the two are fighting… and starts fighting against Goku, shouting for him to give him a turn instead. Freeza, misunderstanding the situation, assumes Vegeta still has a bit of loyalty to him, and tells the Saiyan prince to stand back to let him have his vengeance. Vegeta grudgingly obliges, and Goku and Freeza pause their fight. Freeza is impressed that Goku has improved this much, even if it took him quite a while. Goku senses that Freeza is still hiding something, and Freeza expects the same of him. They agree not to hold back any longer, and Goku goes first, warning Freeza that he won’t want to fight anymore once he sees it. He concentrates, and his hair stands on end as he is enveloped by an ethereal blue aura. Goku says it’s hard to explain, but basically it’s Super Saiyan with the power of Super Saiyan God. Freeza is glad, then, that he decided to attempt attaining a further transformation. Freeza concentrates, and powers up a great deal, surrounding himself in a blinding light. Freeza acknowledges the cheap name, but refers to it as “Golden Freeza” anyway. Goku is impressed, but it also makes him excited. Goku offers to let Vegeta fight now, but he nervously declines, saying that Freeza’s opponent is Kakarrot. The battle begins in earnest this time, and is much more evenly matched than before. Beerus notes that Vegeta isn’t fighting together with Goku, and that the two of them are just too proud. Beerus calls them both fools, which Whis says is just like the God himself. As he begins to lose the battle, Goku compliments how amazing Freeza is, to have come so far when it took him so long to get this strong. Freeza is apparently tickled by this, but says it won’t do him any good. It is then, however, that Freeza notices the presence of Beerus, who complains that Freeza is going to get dust all over the food if he doesn’t fight somewhere else. Goku thinks Freeza should quit while he’s ahead and go home: after all, they’ve spotted his weak point. Freeza is incredulous, but Vegeta pointedly explains that Freeza, consumed with the idea of revenge, probably came to Earth as soon as he achieved his “Golden Freeza” form. He hasn’t had time to get used to it, so it’s rapidly consuming his strength. After holding him under water for a bit, Freeza sends a volley of energy blasts after Goku, who manages to evade or deflect them all. Finally, Freeza manages to land a solid punch directly to Goku’s face… but Goku is completely unfazed. Finally, Goku launches a massive Kamehameha at Freeza, which he attempts to repel with a blast of his own. It is no use, however; the tyrant is utterly defeated. As Goku stands above him, Freeza hauls himself up on the water’s edge, erupting in rage and humiliation… followed by a smirk. Just then, a bolt of energy comes from behind Freeza and pierces Goku straight through the heart: it was Sorbet with his ring. Freeza then takes out his pent-up rage on Goku, kicking and stomping on his chest repeatedly. Freeza gloats over Goku’s softness, mocking the “bad habit” of letting down his guard that left even his powerful body vulnerable to a mere beam attack. Freeza offers to let Vegeta have the final blow against the Saiyan he hates. Vegeta flies over, calling Goku an idiot for not listening to Whis’ warnings. However, he also refuses to kill him, saying that as much as Goku pisses him off, he needs him around for his own purposes. Freeza attempts to sweeten the deal, by offering to make Vegeta the supreme commander of his forces. However, Vegeta chooses instead to utterly obliterate Freeza. There’s no way he’d have any loyalty to the one who destroyed Planet Vegeta! Vegeta tells Kuririn to give Kakarrot the last senzu, or else he’ll die. Kuririn does so, but Freeza tries to interfere, sending energy blasts towards them. However, Vegeta deflects them away, and one ends up killing Sorbet in a fitting comeuppance. Goku thanks Vegeta for saving him; Vegeta scoffs, and says in exchange, he’ll be taking the best part of the fight. Vegeta powers up, and reveals that he can also use the form Goku demonstrated earlier. Freeza freaks out, and unleashes a torrent of energy blasts at Vegeta, but to no avail. What follows is a one-sided beating in which Freeza is humiliated even further, to the point that he even loses his much-vaunted “Golden” form. Back in his fourth form, he pounds against the ground in despair. Standing before Freeza, Vegeta prepares to deliver the final blow… Freeza sends a ball of energy straight into the ground below him. The Earth’s crust cracks and distorts, revealing magma underneath that rushes to the surface. Earth is engulfed in fire, and explodes in a giant shockwave. Only Beerus, Whis, and those near them survive the destruction, thanks to Whis’ barrier. Goku laments not finishing Freeza off when he had the chance. “In that case… why don’t you?” asks Whis, as Beerus tells Goku it was his softness that invited Freeza’s victory. Goku asks what Whis means, and he responds that he will be turning back time. Goku had best hurry, as he can only go back three minutes. He taps his staff twice on the ground, and the events are undone. Once again, Freeza is on his hands and knees, with Vegeta preparing to deal the final blow. As Freeza shouts his retort, Goku screams “FREEZA!” and hits him full-force with a massive Kamehameha. Freeza screams in defeat as his body is completely disintegrated. The moment of relief is broken by Vegeta shouting at Kakarrot for stealing the coup de grâce out from under him. Goku apologizes as Vegeta chews him out for not switching out like he said he would, but Bulma tells him it’s all right, and that Son-kun actually saved him. Vegeta demands an explanation. Beerus says it’s unbecoming for a God of Destruction to restore a planet, but Bulma says that as thanks, she’ll prepare them a feast… as soon as they restore North City with the Dragon Balls, that is. Whis is pleased. Bulma asks Jaco if it’s really all right for him not to be arresting Whis, since control over time is a serious offense. Even after having things explained to him, Vegeta is less than pleased. Goku tries to add that, like Whis said, if they’d simply fought together from the beginning, none of that would have happened in the first place. Vegeta refuses point blank, saying he’d never do that. Goku laughs and says he feels the same way. Vegeta notes it’s the first time they’ve shared the same opinion on something. After the credits, the angels and stuffed toys in Hell gather around the tree, shouting “Welcome back!” Freeza is back where he started, suspended once more in his pod.

text: I will probably watch this only once when it becomes shown in English. The voices like in the trailer would just make me want to laugh and turn it off early, due to the squeaky nature of like Goku for example. The cell saga at least had people be more serious in their fighting and the comedy was not in so many awkward spots. Minus some of the Hercule moments. Even DB had some serious parts in it, where battles were quite rough. Goku had his time in DB and DBZ. We need Vegeta being the main hero. Also for the upcoming dbz rebirth series, we need other characters to shine against main villains. Almost had hope for Tien in dbz but yet he didn't finish off a main villain. We all know how weak Yamcha ended up being. Maybe we should see a series with the past Saiyan Race in it before they meet Frieza. Also have it showing grandpa Gohan when he was younger, along with Master Roshi before he became a major pervert. text: Peace has returned to Earth following the battle with God of Destruction Beerus in the previous movie. With their power dwindling due to the absence of their leader, the remnants of Frieza's army are led by an alien named Sorbet, who decides to revive their master. He then sets off to Earth with one other minion, Tagoma, where they convince Emperor Pilaf, Mai, and Shu, who have collected the Dragon Balls to let them summon Shenron instead. As Shenron is unable to fully revive Frieza, he brings him back to life in pieces, and his minions put him together using their advanced technology. As soon as Frieza's body is regenerated, he emerges in his first form and announces to his soldiers that he will not be satisfied until Goku and Future Trunks have both been killed. Tagoma then says that Frieza should just ignore Goku and the other Saiyans, then Frieza angrily kills Tagoma with a quick Ki blast. Sorbet informs Frieza that Goku's power has surpassed that of even Majin Buu, which is far more than Frieza could have ever imagined. But due to him being a prodigy, Frieza states that through several months of serious training, he would be able to unlock his dormant power and would wipe out the Saiyans in the blink of an eye.  Jaco the Galactic Patrolman travels to earth to warn Bulma that Frieza is approaching, and she gathers the Z Fighters to fight him. Gohan doesn't tell Goten and Trunks about the fight, because they might do something rash. Yamcha and Chiaotzu (who sensed Frieza's revival earlier) are asked by Tien to stay away from the fight as he fears that Frieza's new power may be too dangerous for them to handle. Majin Buu is also absent, for he is in a deep sleep. Goku and Vegeta are training on Beerus' planet with Whis, unaware that Frieza has been revived.  Gohan, Piccolo, Tien, Jaco, Krillin, and Master Roshi clash with an army of at least a thousand of Frieza's soldiers, led by Shisami. Frieza's power in his first form is said to be in a different league than the Z Fighters present on Earth, for he was able to knock out Gohan with a single blast.  Bulma's message eventually reaches Whis, and Goku and Vegeta travel back to earth to fight Frieza. Whis and Beerus join them in order to eat a strawberry-flavored dessert Bulma has prepared for them. Goku fights Frieza in his new "Saiyan beyond God" state and Frieza cannot win in his fourth form at full power. Goku then transforms into Super Saiyan God Super Saiyan and Frieza transforms into a new "Golden Frieza" form. Goku ultimately gains the upper hand, but he is blasted in the chest by Sorbet. Frieza stands over the incapacitated Goku and offers Vegeta a chance to kill Goku for him in exchange for his own life. Vegeta refuses and transforms into a Super Saiyan God Super Saiyan as well, much to Frieza's shock. Vegeta tells Krillin to revive Goku with a Senzu bean. As the latter moves to do so, Frieza attacks him, but Vegeta intercepts and deflects Frieza's attack towards Sorbet, which kills him. Vegeta attacks Frieza, eventually causing him to revert back to his fourth form, who then realizes that he cannot win. Frieza decides to destroy the planet, killing Vegeta in the process.  Earth is destroyed, but Whis creates a bubble around a small piece of rock to protect himself, Beerus, Bulma, Krillin, Gohan, Goku, Master Roshi, Piccolo, Tien and Jaco. While Bulma despairs, Goku expresses his regret that he didn't kill Frieza when he had the chance. Whis tells him that he has the power to set back time but only three minutes earlier. He does so, and they arrive back right before Frieza destroys the Earth. Goku immediately attacks with a God Kamehameha and kills Frieza.

text: As other people have already written Frieza gaining such a crazy power up in just 4 months makes no sense. Frieza even stated that his power had diminished since he died to Goku & Trunks meaning his current power after being revived is less than it was when he got beaten. Also Goku's original super saiyan transformation when he fought Frieza was much weaker than it is now after all the training to make it feel natural to be in Super Saiyan form (yet was still enough to beat Frieza). Super Saiyan 3 is worlds apart from even upgraded super saiyan level and since then goku has been training non stop. He even became a god and his body remembered that feeling. Frieza was always my favourite villain in the dbz universe but this is too much. It would be cooler if he snuck into the hyperbolic time chamber and trained for 2 years or something like that, that would at least make more sense than 4 months. I already have a guess of how the films story will turn out, Goku will have an epic fight with the newly powered up Frieza but will get beaten, Vegeta will then go into God mode because he said in the battle of gods film next time it's my turn. He will still loose and Frieza will start laughing whilst charging up a huge energy attack to blow up the earth, everyone will give their remaining energy to Goku who will finish him with a massive Kamehameha or spirit bomb... Still really looking forward to it though :)
